I guess this is the speech that got Debs in trouble.

from <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eugene_V._Debs#Later_life_and_death" rel="nofollow">wikipedia</a>:
<blockquote>On June 16, 1918, Debs made a speech in Canton, Ohio urging resistance to the military draft of World War I. He was arrested on June 30 and charged with 10 counts of sedition.</blockquote>
